Global Vitamins and Minerals Market Insights
Vitamins and Minerals Market size was valued at USD 140 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 210 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 6.5% from 2024 to 2030.

Vitamins and Minerals Market Overview
The global vitamins and minerals market was valued at approximately USD 43.03 billion in 2024 and is projected to grow at a CAGR of 6.5% from 2024 to 2030. This steady growth is driven by the increasing consumer awareness regarding health and wellness, particularly in relation to vitamins and minerals’ role in disease prevention and overall health maintenance. The market is highly influenced by the rising trend of dietary supplements and fortified food products. The demand for these products is expanding rapidly due to their perceived benefits in promoting immunity, energy levels, and overall well-being.

